# Cloudflare Workers: no catch-all redirect needed.
#
# All app routes (/, /impressum, /datenschutz, /bav-rechner, /etf-vs-bav,
# /riester-rechner, /altersvorsorgedepot-rechner,
# /riester-vs-altersvorsorgedepot, /basisrente-rechner,
# /private-rentenversicherung-rechner, /rente-netto-berechnen,
# /altersvorsorgeprodukte-vergleichen, /rentenluecke-rechner) are prerendered
# as static files and served directly by the Workers asset binding.
# Unknown URLs get Workers' native 404 — no _redirects rule required.
#
# A "/* /404.html 200" catch-all loops on Cloudflare Workers because the
# rewritten request also matches /* and cycles indefinitely. Workers validates
# _redirects and rejects 404 as a target status (valid: 200, 301-303, 307, 308),
# so a proper 404-returning catch-all is not possible via _redirects alone.
# Use wrangler.toml not_found_handling = "404-page" if a custom 404 page is
# needed for unknown paths.
